  "text": "Proof: First, we show that, for s ∈ S and π s ∈ Δ(s), the set defined asZ s = {E μs (p s , r s ,ũ s )|μ s ∈C s } is convex and compact. The convexity can be easily shown, which is omitted due to space constraints (see [CITATION_1] for details). To show the compactness, notice thatC s is weakly closed (i.e., closed w.r.t. to the weak topology) since the feasible set of each of constraint is weakly closed which implies their intersection is also weakly closed. Thus,Z s is closed since it is the image ofC s under expectation (which is a continuous function). This impliesZ s is compact since O ns s is bounded and henceZ s is bounded. Finally, since Z s is the projection onto the first two coordinates of set Z s , its convexity and compactness thus follow.",
